\right]
\end{aligned}
```

We call the right-hand side of the greater-than-or-equal sign the evidence lower bound:

```math
\begin{aligned}
\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{ELBO}}(x_0)
&=\mathbb{E}_{X_{1:T}\sim Q_{1:T}(\cdot\mid x_0)}
\left[
\log
\frac{
p_{0:T}(x_0,X_{1:T})
}{
q_{1:T}(X_{1:T}\mid x_0)
}
\right]
\end{aligned}
```

Then:
$`\log p_0(x_0)\ge\mathcal{L}_{\mathrm{ELBO}}(x_0)`$
Briefly introduce Bayes’ formula:

```math
P(A\mid B)
=
\frac{
P(B\mid A)P(A)
}{
P(B)
}
```

When conditioning on B and C, we have:

```math
P(A\mid B,C)
=
\frac{
P(B\mid A,C)P(A\mid C)
}{
P(B\mid C)
},\quad \text{(treating C as the background condition)}
```

If we treat B as the background condition, then:

```math
P(A\mid B,C)=\frac{
P(C\mid A,B)P(A\mid B)
}{
P(C\mid B)
